Rembrandt (The Hidden Masters)
MasterWorks Press | 1984 | ISBN 717270933 | English | 216 pages | PDF | 41 MB

Although the paintings of Rembrandt are today acknowledged as being among the masterpieces of European art, this is a relatively new appreciation of his work. During his lifetime, his work was consistently underrated when compared with that of Rubens; even in the nineteenth century, John Ruskin, the art critic, wrote, "It is the aim of the best painters to paint the noblest things they can see by sunlight.
